Load data:

# Set working directory to source file location
setwd("~/Box Sync/Research/CRC BMI Meta/Compiled Code & Results/Microbial Function")
load("~/Box Sync/Research/CRC BMI Meta/Compiled Code & Results/Data/functional.16S.wk2.RData")
load("~/Box Sync/Research/CRC BMI Meta/Compiled Code & Results/Data/functional.WGS.wk2.RData")
# arguments: data = dataset in the form from Jun's functional analysis
# conversion df_name = a character of the dataset name for identification
# func_id = id of the function of interest grp_var = variable to group
# boxplots by subset_var = variable to subset data by subset_var_cat = which
# category to subset by subset_opp = should subsetting being the negation of
# the supplied subsetting category?  per.diff.test = logical, should a test
# to compare the functional between groups be executed?
plot_microbial_function <- function(data, df_name, func_id, grp_var, subset_var = NULL, 
    subset_var_cat = NULL, subset_opp = FALSE, per.diff.test = FALSE, seq.type = "WGS", 
    nfactors = 1, grp_var2 = NULL) {
    
    # df_name <- 'baxter' data <- mydata[[df_name]] func_id <-
    # 'L3_Biotin_metabolism' grp_var <- 'BMI' subset_var <- 'Status'
    # subset_var_cat <- 'CRC' subset_opp <- F per.diff.test <- F seq.type <-
    # '16S'
    
    # intializations
    data <- mydata[[df_name]]
    key <- paste0(df_name, ".", subset_var_cat)
    if (subset_opp == T) 
        key <- paste0(df_name, ".non", subset_var_cat)
    # bp <- list()
    diff.test <- list()
    
    
    # first convert to phyloseq object and then use psmelt to data in a usable
    # form with the metadata in a useful place.
    if (seq.type == "16S") {
        my.otu <- otu_table(data$abund.list$KEGG_L3, taxa_are_rows = T)
    } else if (seq.type == "WGS") {
        my.otu <- otu_table(data$abund.list$Module, taxa_are_rows = T)
    } else {
        cat("ERROR!\n")
        cat("OTU Table not found: Check the abundance tables for appropriate kegg level")
        break
    }
    my.sampledata <- data$meta.dat  # meta data
    
    if (grp_var == "BMI_Cat") {
        # grp_var <- 'BMI_Cat'
        my.sampledata$BMI_Cat <- my.sampledata$BMI
        my.sampledata$BMI_Cat[my.sampledata$BMI_Cat < 30] <- 0  # non-Obese
        my.sampledata$BMI_Cat[my.sampledata$BMI_Cat >= 30] <- 1  # Obese
        my.sampledata$BMI_Cat <- factor(my.sampledata$BMI_Cat, labels = c("Non-Obese", 
            "Obese"))
    }
    
    my.sampledata <- sample_data(my.sampledata)
    phy <- merge_phyloseq(my.otu, my.sampledata)
    
    dat <- psmelt(phy)
    
    # ===================================================== #
    # ===================================================== # IMPORTANT:
    # extracts the relavent function
    dat <- dat[grep(func_id, dat$OTU), ]
    # ===================================================== #
    # ===================================================== #
    
    # subsetting
    if (is.null(subset_var) == F) {
        if (subset_opp == T) {
            subdat <- dat[which(dat[, colnames(dat) == subset_var] != subset_var_cat), 
                ]
        } else {
            if (length(subset_var_cat) == 2) {
                subdat <- dat[which(dat[, colnames(dat) == subset_var] == subset_var_cat[1] & 
                  dat[, colnames(dat) == subset_var] == subset_var_cat[2]), 
                  ]
            } else if (length(subset_var_cat) == 1) {
                subdat <- dat[which(dat[, colnames(dat) == subset_var] == subset_var_cat), 
                  ]
            }
        }
    } else {
        subdat <- dat
        # cat('No subsetting was performed\n')
    }
    
    # Make boxplot
    if (nfactors == 1) {
        bp <- ggplot(subdat, aes_string(x = grp_var, y = "Abundance", color = grp_var)) + 
            geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) + geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes_string(fill = grp_var, 
            color = grp_var), position = position_jitterdodge()) + theme_minimal() + 
            coord_flip()
    } else if (nfactors == 2) {
        bp <- ggplot(subdat, aes_string(x = grp_var, y = "Abundance", color = grp_var2)) + 
            geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) + geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes_string(x = grp_var, 
            color = grp_var2), position = position_jitterdodge()) + theme_minimal() + 
            coord_flip()
    }
    
    
    if (per.diff.test == T) {
        outcome <- "Abundance"
        formula <- as.formula(paste(outcome, paste(grp_var, collapse = " + "), 
            sep = " ~ "))
        diff.test[[key]] <- wilcox.test(formula, data = subdat)
        out <- list(bp, dat, diff.test)
        names(out) <- c("boxplots", "data", "Differential Test")
    } else {
        out <- list(bp, dat)
        names(out) <- c("Boxplot", "data")
    }
    
    return(out)
}

First I’ll work on the Urea Cycle function, which can only be found in the WGS data sets.

mydata <- list(feng = Feng.data.obj.wk, voghtmann = Voghtmann.data.obj.wk, zeller = Zeller.data.obj.wk)
urea <- list()

dfs <- c("feng", "voghtmann", "zeller")

for (df in dfs) {
    key <- paste0(df, ".", "CRC")
    urea[[key]] <- plot_microbial_function(mydata, df, func_id = "M00029:", 
        grp_var = "BMI_Cat", subset_var = "Status", subset_var_cat = "CRC", 
        )
    key <- paste0(df, ".", "nonCRC")
    urea[[key]] <- plot_microbial_function(mydata, df, func_id = "M00029:", 
        grp_var = "BMI_Cat", subset_var = "Status", subset_var_cat = "CRC", 
        subset_opp = T)
    key <- paste0(df, ".", "normal")
    urea[[key]] <- plot_microbial_function(mydata, df, func_id = "M00029:", 
        grp_var = "BMI_Cat", subset_var = "Status", subset_var_cat = "Normal")
}
